257
00:14:30,041 --> 00:14:38,160
Rym: So as we mentioned at the start, today's show is going to be about Otakon and the, I guess, hullabaloo around their new pending, uh, artist alley policy.

258
00:14:38,561 --> 00:14:53,840
Scott: For those of you who might not be informed, the policy is referring to the sale and I guess also the display of fan art or, you know, reuse of copyrighted characters from anime and manga in the artist alley of Otakon.

259
00:14:54,501 --> 00:15:03,377
Rym: Now, basically what happened was, on a Wednesday I believe, in a thread titled official changes to Otakon's artist alley policy or something like that.

260
00:15:03,518 --> 00:15:04,388
Scott: On the Otakon forums.

261
00:15:04,429 --> 00:15:11,357
Rym: Yeah, on the Otakon forums, they made an announcement as to all the changes to the artist alley and things like tables are six feet wide now and all this other stuff.

262
00:15:11,459 --> 00:15:17,419
Rym: But tucked away in there, number five, after a large, bold thing that says this is the big one, is the following policy.

263
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:22,732
Rym: Otakon's artist alley will be actively disallowing the sale of unlicensed copyrighted materials.

264
00:15:23,196 --> 00:15:24,509
Rym: If you own it, you can sell it.

265
00:15:24,853 --> 00:15:26,569
Rym: If you have a license to it, you can sell it.

266
00:15:26,892 --> 00:15:29,134
Rym: But if it has material, images, sounds, etc.

267
00:15:29,255 --> 00:15:35,196
Rym: in whole or in part, in which you do not have permission to sell, then that material will not be allowed in the artist alley.

268
00:15:35,479 --> 00:15:38,569
Rym: Anyone found a violation will lose their space, blah blah blah blah blah.

269
00:15:39,236 --> 00:15:46,598
Rym: And then an addendum, the policy for display of unlicensed copyrighted material provided that it is not for sale is currently under review.

270
00:15:47,822 --> 00:15:49,579
Scott: Now this is such a big deal because

271
00:15:50,124 --> 00:15:50,548
Guest: while

272
00:15:50,690 --> 00:16:17,111
Scott: artist alley at Otakon and many other conventions has plenty of original artwork such as web comic artists and people making their own print comics and all sorts of other original works of art, much of it and much of the money is in the sale of fan art which is basically you take existing characters that you did not create and you draw them or write them or whatever into new

273
00:16:17,131 --> 00:16:17,737
Rym: stories

274
00:16:18,322 --> 00:16:19,534
Scott: or pictures or whatever.

275
00:16:19,897 --> 00:16:25,378
Rym: Now bear in mind that fan art, while it's a word that we all use, is not a legal definition by any means.

276
00:16:26,321 --> 00:16:34,340
Rym: And the people who are responsible for this decision and most of the people in the debate are very strongly urging that people shouldn't use that word and they should use more defined terms.

277
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:39,087
Scott: Yeah, I guess fan art could just mean art created by a fan.

278
00:16:39,147 --> 00:16:45,369
Scott: I mean you could have a spinning blades somehow making art and you know call that fan art.

279
00:16:45,874 --> 00:16:54,965
